Turkey Meatloaf
  -- America's Test Kitchen

Loaf:
3 tbsp unsalted butter
pinch baking soda
1/2 onion, chopped fine
1/4 tsp salt
1 garlic clove
1 tsp fresh thyme
2 tbsp worcesteshire
2 egg yolks
2 tbsp dijon mustard
3 tbsp quick oats (or old-fashioned, chopped finely)
2 tsp cornstarch
3/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp  pepper
3/4 c chopped parsley
1/2 c parmesan cheese
2 lb ground turkey (85-93%)

Melt butter in saute pan, add baking soda, onion, and salt. Saute until soft and translucent. Add garlic and thyme, saute for 1 min. Add worcestershire sauce, reduce down. Pour into a bowl and let cool. Add egg yolks, mustard and mix. Add oats, cornstarch, salt, pepper to a bowl and mix; add to onion mixture. Add parsley and and cheese, mix. Add turkey and mix well.

Glaze:
1 c ketchup
1/4 c brown sugar
2 1/2 tsp cider vinegar
1/2 tsp hot sauce

Combine in saucepan over medium heat, cook for 5 min.

Place wire rack in baking sheet, cover with foil. Turn meat onto foil and corm into a loaf, 9x5". Brush half the glaze on the loaf, getting sides as well as top. Bake in 350F oven for 40 min. Take out, add rest of glaze, return to ove for another 35 min. (160F internal temp) Let rest for 20 min before cutting.
